<P><H1 align=center>ADD / EDIT DEPENDANT DETAILS – DC045</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields in red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed 
</FONT>           </P>
<P>This screen collects details about any dependant(s) the applicant may have. 
This is important as may affect the applicant’s level of outgoings and therefore 
ability to repay the loan. Also, if the dependants are over 17 years of age and 
living at the property, they will be required to sign a consent to mortgage 
form</P>
<P><H3>Dependant relative of: </H3>select the name of the 
applicant who has the dependant. This must be completed in order to proceed 
Forenames / 
<P></P>
<P><H3>Surname: </H3>these fields are also mandatory
<P></P>
<P><H3>Date of Birth: </H3>this is not mandatory, however may 
be required further on in the process in case the dependant is over the age of 
17 (see consent to mortgage form)
<P></P>
<P><H3>Dependant is your?: </H3>select from the drop-down list 
the relation the dependant is to the applicant. Eg. grandmother, father, 
daughter etc. 
<P></P>
<P><H3>Resident at new address?: </H3>select the ‘Yes’ or ‘No’ 
radio button. This may affect whether the dependant will need to sign a consent 
to mortgage form
<P></P>
<P><H3>Are there any additional applicants the dependant is related to?: </H3>if it is a joint application and the dependant is related to 
both applicants, click the ‘Yes’ radio button and provide details in the field 
below 
<P></P>
<P><H3>Another: </H3>if there is more than one dependant, 
click on ‘Another’ and complete the details
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>clicking on ‘OK’ leads back to the <A HREF="HELP_DC040.asp">Dependant 
Summary screen (DC040)</A>, where the details entered here will be summarised in the 
main box.
<P></P>

